\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. C. heldreichii} Halácsy, {\i Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  40}: 114 (1890). Biennial 15-100 cm. Stem sparsely arachnoid-lanate to lanate-floccose. Leaf-lobes linear-lanceolate to oblong-lanceolate, with strong apical spine 6-25 mm. Capitula solitary or in a sparingly branched corymb, with 2-6 narrow subtending leaves equalling or somewhat exceeding capitulum. Involucre 25-35 × 20-40(-60) mm; middle bracts gradually narrowed to the cartilaginous, densely spinose-serrulate apex, with slender apical spine 2-6 mm. Corolla 27-30 mm, usually white. Achenes 5-6 mm; pappus 19-25 mm. •{\i  Mountains of Greece.} Gr.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  A rather variable species; the following subspecies seem doubtfully distinct.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b heldreichii}: Leaves attenuate at the base and sessile to narrowly auriculate-semiamplexicaul, not decurrent, arachnoid-lanate to -tomentose beneath. Involucre glabrous to sparsely arachnoid-hairy. Corolla white or pink. {\i C. Greece}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b euboicum} Petrak, {\i Bot. Jahrb.}{\b  80}: 420 (1961): Leaves broadly auriculate-semiamplexicaul, the middle often decurrent for up to 1 cm, sparsely arachnoid-lanate beneath. Involucre arachnoid-lanate. Corolla purplish. {\i Evvoia}.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. C. bulgaricum} DC., {\i Prodr.} {\b 6}: 639 (1838). Biennial 60-100 cm. Leaves arachnoid-lanate beneath; lobes lanceolate to narrowly triangular, with rigid apical spine 3-10(-16) mm. Capitula 3-10 in a lax to dense raceme or corymb, with 2-6(-9) subtending leaves shorter than to equalling capitulum. Involucre 24-35 × 22-35 mm, ovoid-globose, sparsely arachnoid-hairy to subglabrous; outer bracts suberect; middle erecto-patent, slightly widened to the spinose-serrulate apex, with rigid apical spine 1-3·5 mm. Corolla 23-30 mm, purple. Achenes 5-6 mm; pappus 19-22 mm. {\i Woods. Near S.W. coast of Black Sea}. Bu Tu. ({\i Anatolia.})
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 {\b  C. baytopae} P. H. Davis & Parris, {\i Notes Roy. Bot. Gard. Edinb.}{\b  33}: 415 (1975), described from a single gathering from the southern margin of the range of {\b 3} (near Saray), is related to {\b 3} and {\b 4} but has the numerous capitula in a corymb, 1-3 subtending leaves shorter than the capitulum, the involucre 15-20 × 17-23 mm and with patent bracts gradually narrowed to a smooth apex, the corolla 17-18 mm and the pappus 9-14 mm.
\par

