\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. C. polycephalum} DC., {\i Prod.}{\b  6}: 639 (1838). Like {\b 3} but capitula more than 10, in a dense panicle or corymb, with 6-12 subtending leaves equalling or exceeding capitulum; involucre 15-23 × 10-15 mm, subcylindrical; bracts erect, gradually narrowed to the subpatent apex; corolla 13-16 mm, usually white; achenes 3·5-4·5 mm; pappus 13-14 mm.{\i  Turkey-in-Europe} ({\i near Istanbul}). Tu. ({\i Anatolia}.)
\par

