\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. C. lacaitae} Petrak, {\i Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  64}: 456 (1914). Biennial (60-)100-150 cm. Leaves sparsely arachnoid-hairy to -lanate or rarely glabrescent beneath; lobes linear to linear-lanceolate, with strong apical spine 4-13 mm. Capitula few, in a lax corymb, with 1-4 subtending leaves shorter than capitulum. Involucre 30-40 × 30-45(-50) mm, sparsely arachnoid-hairy to subglabrous (rarely villous); bracts erecto-patent to suberect; middle somewhat widened to the purple, sparsely denticulate-ciliate or weakly spinescent apex, with apical spine 2-5 mm. Corolla 29-35 mm, purple; tube longer than limb. Achenes 5-6 mm; pappus 25-30 mm. •{\i  S. Italy} ({\i hills N. of Amalfi}). It.
